#. type: Title ==
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deploying new images"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:3
msgid ""
"This file describes how to deploy a new image on selected terminals first, "
"test it, and then deploy it to all terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The hardware type group (i.e. [literal]``HWTYPE`` group) is used for booting "
"new terminals, while already deployed terminals can be moved to any group "
"that provides the {saltboot} formula.  This flexibility allows for testing "
"of new images or configurations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Dual group image deployment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:6
msgid "Build new image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:7
msgid ""
"Use image synchronization formula to synchronize the image to all Branch "
"Servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:8
msgid "Create a test group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Name the group, for example, [literal]``TEST:POSVendor-Terminal``. The name "
"can be chosen freely."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:10
msgid ""
"Add the {saltboot} formula to this group.  Use the same configuration as in "
"the original hardware type group ([literal]``HWTYPE``), except for the image "
"version.  Use the name and version of the new image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:11
msgid "Move selected terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:12
msgid "Identify the terminals you want to test the new image on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Transfer these terminals from the group [literal]``HWTYPE:POSVendor-"
"Terminal`` group to the newly created group [literal]``TEST:POSVendor-"
"Terminal``.  It is recommended to use System Set Manager for this task."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:14
msgid "Reboot terminals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:15
msgid "Power on the selected POS terminals.  They should boot the new image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:16
msgid "Verify and evaluate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Monitor the terminals in the [literal]``TEST:POSVendor-Terminal`` group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Check if the new image performs as expected and if there are any issues or "
"errors encountered."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:19
msgid "Update [literal]``HWTYPE`` group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:20
msgid ""
"Once you have confirmed that the new image works correctly, the "
"[literal]``HWTYPE`` group can be updated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:21
msgid ""
"Modify the image version in the [literal]``HWTYPE:POSVendor-Terminal`` group "
"to match the tested and approved version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:22
msgid "This ensures that all other terminals receive the new image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Controlling image versions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:24
msgid ""
"By default, {saltboot} formula selects the specified image name and version "
"or selects the highest one if the version is not specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:25
msgid ""
"There are multiple methods to control the image version within the "
"[literal]``HWTYPE`` and [literal]``TEST`` groups:"
msgstr ""

#. .Procedure: Image control
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:26
msgid "Specify exact version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:27
msgid ""
"In both the [literal]``HWTYPE`` and [literal]``TEST`` groups, specify "
"explicitly the exact version of the image to be deployed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:28
msgid "Make sure that the specified image version is already synchronized."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:29
msgid "Mark new image as [literal]``Inactive``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:30
msgid "In the [literal]``HWTYPE`` group, do not specify the image version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:31
msgid ""
"Mark the new image as [literal]``Inactive`` after building and before "
"synchronizing it to Branch Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:32
msgid ""
"The [literal]``Inactive`` flag ensures, that the image is not auto-selected "
"when the image version is not specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:33
msgid ""
"After testing, remove the [literal]``Inactive`` flag so the image can be "
"auto-selected in the [literal]``HWTYPE`` group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:34
msgid ""
"The [literal]``Inactive`` flag can be accessed through the API.  For more "
"information, see xref:retail:retail-image-pillars.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:35
msgid "Utilize [literal]``Freeze Image`` flag."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:36
msgid "In the [literal]``HWTYPE`` group, omit the image version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:37
msgid ""
"Before synchronizing the new image, set the [literal]``Freeze Image`` flag "
"in {saltboot} formula in [literal]``HWTYPE`` group.  This ensures that the "
"already deployed terminals in this group will keep the old image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:38
msgid "Synchronize and test the new image in the [literal]``TEST`` group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:39
msgid ""
"Reset the [literal]``Freeze Image`` flag in [literal]``HWTYPE`` group, so "
"the terminals in this group will be updated to the new image too."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/retail/pages/retail-best-practices.adoc:40
msgid ""
"Do not use the whitelist in Image Synchronization formula to control which "
"terminal boots which image.  It does not provide the required granularity "
"and does not work with containerized Branch Server."
msgstr ""

